<plot>When 'David Lean (I)' (qv) made his film _Doctor Zhivago (1965)_ (qv), he realized that it would be impossible to do location shooting in Moscow. Instead, he found a location on the plains outside Madrid, Spain and built a set to look like the Russian capital. This promotional film gives viewers a short look at the set under construction.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?377919</url></doc>
